OL,3,CWidow, 95, goes to court with scholar
OL,4,Cover washing in communal garden
OL,6,FTwo neighbours have taken a dispute
OL,7,Fover washing to court after one of
OL,8,Fthem objected to laundry being hung
OL,9,Fout to dry in the communal garden.
OL,11,FRevd Canon Professor Richard Burridge,
OL,12,Fwho is an internationally recognised
OL,13,Fbiblical scholar and theologian, uses
OL,14,Ftwo rotary washing lines in the garden
OL,15,Fshared by residents in the luxury
OL,16,FTrews Weir Court apartments in Exeter.
OL,18,FLotte Grant, a 95-year-old widow who
OL,19,Fhas lived at the Grade II property for
OL,20,F30 years, said the use of the lines is
OL,21,Fa breach of the terms of the lease.
