OL,3,CWidow, 95, goes to court with scholar
OL,4,Cover washing in communal garden
OL,6,FRevd Burridge said Mrs Grant cannot
OL,7,Fsee the washing lines from her
OL,8,Fapartment, and said drying washing in
OL,9,Fthe flats caused mould due to problems
OL,10,Fwith the damp as the building is
OL,11,Flocated next to the river Exe in
OL,12,FExeter.
OL,14,FThe management company Trews Weir
OL,15,FCourt Management Ltd said the lines
OL,16,Fwere compliant with the lease, and a
OL,17,Fjudge at a previous hearing ruled in
OL,18,Ffavour of the company. Mrs Grant has
OL,19,Fappealed his judgement.
